2. Import data

Because differential analysis includes the calculations of means, the data to be used in this section is the normalized untransformed data

# set path variables
project_dir <- getwd()
project_name <- 'RP_All_1154'
figures_dir <- file.path(project_dir, paste0(project_name, '_output_figures'))
tables_dir <- file.path(project_dir,  paste0(project_name, '_output_tables'))
norm_auc_table_file <- file.path(tables_dir, 'normalized_untransformed_auc_table.csv')
norm_auc_table_nogap_file <- file.path(tables_dir, 'normalized_untransformed_auc_table_nogap.csv')
# If the flag was setted before, nothing needs to be changed here, the correct file will be automatically used

  compounds_table_file <- file.path(tables_dir, 'compounds_table.csv')


# Load auc_table

norm.matrix <- read_csv(norm_auc_table_nogap_file)
norm.matrix <- column_to_rownames(norm.matrix, var = '...1')

norm.matrix_nogap <- read_csv(norm_auc_table_nogap_file)
norm.matrix_nogap <- column_to_rownames(norm.matrix_nogap, var = '...1')

# Load compounds table and add a column that has names for identified compounds and FeatureID for the rest (for plotting puRPouses)

3. Calculate ratios and log2fold-change

3.1 Get samples per each treatment


# Get the average AUC per each of the treatments
## Get samples per treatment

ERLE.samples <- get_samples(metadata, Treatment = 'Plant', value = 'ERLE')
ERIN.samples <- get_samples(metadata, Treatment = 'Plant', value = 'ERIN')
BOCU.samples <- get_samples(metadata, Treatment = 'Plant', value = 'BOCU')
LEDU.samples <- get_samples(metadata, Treatment = 'Plant', value = 'LEDU')
CTRL.samples <- get_samples(metadata, Treatment = 'Fungi', value = 'CTRL')

3.2 Get table of differentially expressed features per each comparison

The following function will calculate ratio, log2FC, p values and adjusted pvalues. If no replicates are available for EACH treatment please use the get_diff_table_no_pval() function


# The following function will calculate ratio, log2FC, p values and adjusted pvalues. If no replicates are available for EACH treatment
# please use the get_diff_table_no_pval() function

ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table <- get_diff_table(norm.matrix, treatment.sample_list = ERLE.samples, control.sample_list = CTRL.samples, log2_transformed = TRUE)
ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table <- get_diff_table(norm.matrix, treatment.sample_list = ERIN.samples, control.sample_list = CTRL.samples, log2_transformed = TRUE)
BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table <- get_diff_table(norm.matrix, treatment.sample_list = BOCU.samples, control.sample_list = CTRL.samples, log2_transformed = TRUE)
LEDU_to_CTRL.diff_table <- get_diff_table(norm.matrix, treatment.sample_list = LEDU.samples, control.sample_list = CTRL.samples, log2_transformed = TRUE)

Merge differentially expressed features with the annotation


# Create dataframes for the up and downregulated metabolites at each time point and merge them with the compound information

ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table <- compounds_table %>% 
  select( - contains('Results'), -SampleID, -AUC,  -Fungi, - Plant) %>% 
  right_join(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table, by = 'FeatureID') %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  filter(!is.nan(log2FC)) %>% 
  mutate(Comment = case_when(log2FC < 0 ~ 'Downregulated',
                             log2FC > 0 ~ 'Upregulated'))

ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$Comment <- factor(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$Comment, 
                               levels = c( 'Downregulated', 'Upregulated' ))

table_file <- file.path(tables_dir, 'Diff_expressed_ERLE.csv')
write_csv(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table, table_file )

ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table<- compounds_table %>% 
  select(-contains('Annotation Source:'), - contains('Results'), -SampleID, -AUC, -Plant, - Fungi) %>%
  right_join(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table, by = 'FeatureID') %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  filter(!is.nan(log2FC)) %>% 
  mutate(Comment = case_when(log2FC < 0 ~ 'Downregulated',
                             log2FC > 0 ~ 'Upregulated'))

ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table$Comment <- factor(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table$Comment, 
                               levels = c( 'Downregulated', 'Upregulated'))

table_file <- file.path(tables_dir, 'Diff_expressed_ERIN.csv')
write_csv(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table, table_file )

BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table <- compounds_table %>% 
  select(-contains('Annotation Source:'), - contains('Results'), -SampleID, -AUC, -Plant, -Fungi) %>% 
  right_join(BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table, by = 'FeatureID') %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  filter(!is.nan(log2FC)) %>% 
  mutate(Comment = case_when(log2FC < 0 ~ 'Downregulated',

sig_features <- c(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$FeatureID[ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval < 0.05],

4. Plots of dysregulated features

4.1 Number of dysregulated features in each group

# removed pval adj to regular pval
num_diff_features <- tibble(Comparison = rep(c('ERLE_to_CTRL', 'ERIN_to_CTRL', 'BOCU_to_CTRL', 'LEDU_to_CTRL'), each = 2),
                            Type = rep(c('Name', 'No name'), 4),
                            count = 0)
num_diff_features$Type <- factor(num_diff_features$Type, levels = c('No name', 'Name'))

num_diff_features[1, 3] <- sum(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval < 0.05 & !is.na(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[2, 3] <- sum(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval < 0.05 & is.na(ERLE_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[3, 3] <- sum(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval < 0.05 & !is.na(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[4, 3] <- sum(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval< 0.05 & is.na(ERIN_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[5, 3] <- sum(BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval < 0.05 & !is.na(BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[6, 3] <- sum(BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval< 0.05 & is.na(BOCU_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[5, 3] <- sum(LEDU_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval< 0.05 & !is.na(LEDU_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)
num_diff_features[6, 3] <- sum(LEDU_to_CTRL.diff_table$pval < 0.05 & is.na(LEDU_to_CTRL.diff_table$Name), na.rm = TRUE)

num_diff_plot <- ggplot(num_diff_features)+
  geom_bar(aes(y=count, x=Comparison,fill= Type), stat="identity", alpha=0.7)+
  theme_classic()+xlab("Comparison")+ylab("Count")
